description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Exciting opportunities on Willows ward!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Want to be part of a friendly, excited and energised team?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Willows Ward team are looking for a Charge Nurse - Band 6 to work on Willows Ward at the Woodlands Hospital in Ipswich.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be joining a friendly, motivated and enthusiastic team who are on their journey to outstanding. Willows is the Woodlands older adults inpatient service&#39;s. We provide 21 beds for both individuals with a diagnosis of dementia and functional disorders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be joining the team who are currently taking part in the Trust Quality Improvement programme for reducing restrictive practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are looking for?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are a Band 6 looking to gain experience in a different area and want to widen your expertise then this could be perfect!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Or if you are a band 5 looking to further develop your career and professional development then apply now!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Not sure? &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Don’t worry, you will be given extensive support from our fantastic Ward Manager and Modern Matron as well as from the rest of the team who are already excited to meet you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Have we got you interested? Sign me up!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please complete and submit the application form via NSFT vacancies or NHS jobs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have any questions please contact Ronnie Torkornoo, Ward Manager to talk through this exciting opportunity on 01473 891780.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Benefits included with this role are:-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS pension&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;a comprehensive in house &amp; external training programmes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;career progression&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;starting annual leave of 27 days per annum increasing to 33 days pa based on length of service (plus paid bank holidays)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;staff physio service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS discounts and many more.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here at NSFT we pride ourselves on being a welcoming, talented, friendly and supportive team who like nothing better than sharing their experiences and learning from each other.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please find attached our Job Description and Person Specification for more detail on your Key Accountabilities, then if you feel you have what it takes to make a difference in your local communities, click APPLY!&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Interviews are provisionally booked for 19th November 2020, candidates may only be given a minimum of 3 days’ notice, please note this date is provisional and may be subject to change. You will be contacted via email and invited to book a time. These emails may go to your SPAM, so please keep checking all your emails if applying.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please visit our Twitter page @NSFTjobs&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameRonnie TorkornooJob titleWard Manager - Willows wardEmail addressRonnie.torkornoo@nsft.nhs.ukTelephone number01473 891780&lt;/p&gt;
